      "span_text": "The principle of the simulation is based on a random walk around the 3D position and orientation of the nucleus/spindle by 3 center coordinates (x, y, z) and 2 angles (θ and φ). At each iteration one of those variable is changed, the force and torques of all MTs on the nucleus/spindle are calculated and compared to the previous step in order to converge towards an equilibrium of minimal forces and torques [CITATION_1] ."
